						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab in the Karivīrappa temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>(Date lost.)</p>						

						<p>This worn out inscription is dated in the <hi rend="bold">Chālukya-Vikrama</hi> (lost year), <hi rend="bold">Śrāvaṇa Amāvāsyā, Wednesday.</hi> The details are insufficient to find out the Christian equivalent. It records a grant of land for the worship and offerings of a god (name lost). <hi rend="italic">Agrahāra</hi> <hi rend="bold">Kākaṇḍige</hi> (Modern Kākhaṇḍki) and the sub-division of <hi rend="bold">Bāge Fifty</hi> are mentioned. </p>						

						</summary>
